<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-15T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.115 Panay/84: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-15T19:00:00+09:00">December 15, 1937—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 15—8:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>641. Department’s 345, December 14, 11 p.m. Japanese interference with
                            rescue work at Hohsien.</p>
                        <p>Strong oral representations were made to the Foreign Office this
                            evening.</p>
                        <p>My British colleague is taking similar action on the basis of our
                            information.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping for Hankow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>